      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:22:5",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ قَتَلَ مَمْلُوكَتَهُ أَوْ مَمْلُوكَهُ قَالَ إِنْ كَانَ الْمَمْلُوكُ لَهُ أُدِّبَ وَ حُبِسَ إِلَّا أَنْ يَكُونَ مَعْرُوفاً بِقَتْلِ الْمَمَالِيكِ فَيُقْتَلُ بِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from Al Mukhtar Bin Muhammad Bin Al Mukhtar, and Muhammad Bin Al Hassan, from Abdullah Bin Al Hassan Al Alawy, both together, from Al Fatah Bin Yazeed Al Jurjany, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup> regarding a man who kills his slave girl or slave man. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘If it was the owned slave of his, he would be disciplined and imprisoned, except if he happens to be well known with the killing of the slaves, so he would be killed due to it’."
        ]
      }
